Russian Equity Movers: Bank of Moscow, Lukoil and Polyus Gold

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-03-23T16:43:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/russian-equity-movers-bank-of-moscow-lukoil-and-polyus-gold.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  added 1.7
percent to 1,770.56 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index increased 1 percent to 1,997.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  Bank of Moscow (MMBM RX) climbed to a two-week high, rising
7.3 percent to 1,054.6 rubles after RIA Novosti reported
minority shareholders offered to acquire a stake in the lender
that VTB Group previously agreed to buy.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX), Russia’s second-biggest oil producer,
advanced for the first day in three, adding 2.2 percent to
2,016.4 rubles as concern supplies from  Libya  will remain
disrupted pushed oil to a two-week high.  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX),  Russia ’s largest gold producer,
gained for the fourth day in five, rising 2.2 percent to 1,660.4
rubles as gold climbed to near a record in  London . Unrest in
Libya and the Middle East spurred demand for the metal as an
alternative investment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran at 
